---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Chris Hartwig | Vibe Software Engineering"
  description="Learn more about Chris Hartwig, a backend engineer and entrepreneur specializing in devops and SSL/TLS technologies, exploring the intersection of AI and software engineering."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">About Chris Hartwig</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Backend engineer, entrepreneur, and SSL expert exploring the
        intersection of AI and software engineering
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 items-center mb-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-1">
          <img
            src="/og-image.jpg"
            alt="Chris Hartwig"
            class="rounded-xl w-full h-64 object-cover"
            width="400"
            height="400"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-2">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">
            Backend Engineer & Entrepreneur
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            I'm Chris, a developer who has been working remotely from abroad
            since 2014. My journey has taken me across multiple time zones
            (UTC-4 to UTC+8), from the Carribean to Southeast Asia, always with
            a focus on backend engineering, devops, and SSL/TLS technologies.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            I'm the founder of SSLPing.com, launched in 2015 and built into a
            popular service. Since then I've started
            <a href="https://SSLBoard.com" class="text-primary hover:underline" target="_blank">
              SSLBoard.com
            </a>, a platform for auditing and managing SSL/TLS certificates at
            scale. Also
            <a href="https://SSLCalendar.com" class="text-primary hover:underline" target="_blank">
              SSLCalendar.com
            </a>, a tool for managing SSL/TLS certificates expiration dates in a
            regular calendar. And
            <a href="https://QCready.com" class="text-primary hover:underline" target="_blank">
              QCReady.com
            </a>, a tool to evaluate Post-Quantum Cryptography readiness at scale.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">My Journey with Technology</h2>
        <p>
          With years of experience in backend engineering and devops, I've seen
          technology evolve dramatically. From managing distributed systems
          across continents to implementing security protocols, I've navigated
          the complexities of modern software development.
        </p>

        <p>
          My focus has always been on the infrastructure and systems that power
          applications. From SSL/TLS expertise to gaming backend architectures,
          I've worked on the foundations that make digital experiences possible.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3">
          Exploring AI in Software Engineering
        </h3>
        <p>
          Today, I'm fascinated by how artificial intelligence is transforming
          software engineering. As someone who has built complex backend
          systems, I'm particularly interested in how AI tools are changing the
          way we design, build, and maintain software.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-3">Through this blog, I share insights on:</p>

        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
          <li>AI-assisted backend development and devops practices</li>
          <li>
            The impact of AI on security implementations and SSL/TLS
            technologies
          </li>
          <li>How AI tools enhance distributed system design and management</li>
          <li>
            Practical applications of AI in real-world engineering scenarios
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3">
          Remote Engineering & Distributed Systems
        </h3>
        <p>
          My experience building systems while working remotely across multiple
          countries has given me unique perspectives on distributed development
          workflows. I explore how AI tools can enhance collaboration and
          productivity for distributed engineering teams.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 bg-primary/5 p-6 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Interested in AI in Software Engineering?
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          Join my newsletter for weekly insights on how AI is transforming the
          field of software engineering.
        </p>
        <a href="/newsletter/" class="btn-primary inline-flex items-center">
          Subscribe to Newsletter
          <svg
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            class="h-5 w-5 ml-2"
            viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            fill="currentColor"
          >
            <path
              d="M2.003 5.884L10 9.882l7.997-3.998A2 2 0 0016 4H4a2 2 0 00-1.997 1.884z"
            ></path>
            <path d="M18 8.118l-8 4-8-4V14a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8.118z"
            ></path>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

